<DOC><DOCNO> AP890701-0069 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-01-89 1052EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Turkey-Kurds     07-01 0146</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Turkey-Kurds,0149</SECOND><HEAD>Three Kurdish Guerrillas Killed</HEAD><DATELINE>MARDIN, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three Kurdish guerillas were killedSaturday in a clash with security forces, the semi-official Anatolianews agency reported.   The agency said the security forces were conducting a search in amountainous area near the Syrian border when they encountered theguerrillas and ordered them to surrender. The rebels opened fire,the agency said.   Security forces have launched a massive operation in themountains of southeastern Turkey as a result of the increase ofKurdish attacks over the past two months.   Kurdish rebels are fighting for an independent Marxist state inparts of eastern and southeastern Turkey. More than 900 securitypersonnel and civilians and an equal number of insurgents have beenkilled since the Kurds started hit-and-run attacks in 1984, officialreports say.   Ethnic Kurds make up about one-fifth of Turkey's population of 55million.</TEXT></DOC>